.SH NAME
SDL_Condition \- A means to block multiple threads until a condition is satisfied\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_mutex\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "typedef struct SDL_Condition SDL_Condition;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Condition variables, paired with an 
.BR SDL_Mutex
, let an app halt
multiple threads until a condition has occurred, at which time the app can
release one or all waiting threads\[char46]

Wikipedia has a thorough explanation of the concept:

https://en\[char46]wikipedia\[char46]org/wiki/Condition_variable

